headline.main: ALLIES BUILD UP MID-ASIA POWER; Anglo-Soviet Diplomacy Wins Block to Germans at the Caucasus, Japan on East

lead_paragraph: KUIBYSHEV, Russia, Nov. 16 (Delayed) -- While few exact details of its extent are generally known and its development has not been widely advertised, Anglo-Russian cooperation in the Middle Bast has greatly improved the Allied position, not only in that wide area but in the broad relations to the danger in the West and the threatened danger in the Far East.
